2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- KARATKIEVICH, ULADZIMIR (1930-1984) was a Belarusian
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- romantic writer. After his first published work was a poem
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- in 1951, he followed up with novels, short stories, plays,
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- essays, articles and screenplays. His probably most popular
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- work is the novel 'King Stakh's Wild Hunt' (1964). Most his
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- novels are about Belarus's past.  He won many national
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- literary awards and influenced the Belarusian literature's
2019-12-17 19:44:26	--	- development of historical themes.
